      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's interesting you mention that. some people i've talked to say that focusing so much on nonviolence actually ended up being a way for the government to keep things controlled and slow down real progress. do you think the focus on nonviolence was actually the most effective path, or was it more about what the establishment was willing to tolerate?",
